# Restart dev server (port 3000) after changes

When you make code changes in this project (daily-closing-app):

1. **Stop port 3000**: Terminate any process listening on port 3000.
   - **Windows (PowerShell)**: `Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }`
   - **Unix/macOS**: `npx kill-port 3000` (or `lsof -ti:3000 | xargs kill -9` if kill-port not available)
2. **Start dev server**: Run `npm run dev` in the project root (run in background so the terminal stays usable).

Do this after applying changes, without the user having to ask. Skip only if the user explicitly says not to (e.g. "don't restart" or "leave the server running").
